UK ' s Major promises manifesto for long term . Prime Minister John Major on Tuesday pledged the Conservatives ' manifesto for the May 1 election would be a far - reaching one " that sets out substantive long - term policies of what we will do to tackle the issues of the future " . Major told a news conference that while his party ' s policies , in the manifesto to be launched on Wednesday , would be " clear cut , detailed and costed " , those of his opponents would be full of contradictions . " I intend to deal with how to build on the best economy for a generation , how to spread opportunity and prosperity to every home in the country , " Major said . 
